.TH "bio_add_hw_page" 9 "bio_add_hw_page" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bio_add_hw_page \- attempt to add a page to a bio with hw constraints
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" bio_add_hw_page
.BI "(struct request_queue *q "  ","
.BI "struct bio *bio "  ","
.BI "struct page *page "  ","
.BI "unsigned int len "  ","
.BI "unsigned int offset "  ","
.BI "unsigned int max_sectors "  ","
.BI "bool *same_page "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "q" 12
the target queue
.IP "bio" 12
destination bio
.IP "page" 12
page to add
.IP "len" 12
vec entry length
.IP "offset" 12
vec entry offset
.IP "max_sectors" 12
maximum number of sectors that can be added
.IP "same_page" 12
return if the segment has been merged inside the same page
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Add a page to a bio while respecting the hardware max_sectors, max_segment
and gap limitations.
